quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  13,19,"What, is he who knows what is sent down to thee from thy Lord is the truth, like him who is blind? Only men possessed of minds remember"
  13,20,"who fulfil God's covenant, and break not the compact"
  13,21,"who join what God has commanded shall be joined, and fear their Lord, and dread the evil reckoning"
  13,22,"patient men, desirous of the Face of their Lord, who perform the prayer, and expend of that We have provided them, secretly and in public, and who avert evil with good -- theirs shall be the Ultimate Abode"
  13,23,"Gardens of Eden which they shall enter; and those who were righteous of their fathers, and their wives, and their seed, shall enter them, and the angels shall enter unto them from every gate"
  13,24,"Peace be upon you, for that you were patient.' Fair is the Ultimate Abode"
  13,25,"And those who break the covenant of God after His compact, and who snap what God has commanded to be joined, and who work corruption in the earth -- theirs shall be the curse, and theirs the Evil Abode"
  13,26,"God outspreads and straitens His provision unto whomsoever He will. They rejoice in this present life; and this present life, beside the world to come, is naught but passing enjoyment"
  13,27,"The unbelievers say, 'Why has a sign not been sent down upon him from his Lord?' Say: 'God leads astray whomsoever He will, and He guides to Him all who are penitent"
  13,28,"Those who believe, their hearts being at rest in God's remembrance -- in God's remembrance are at rest the hearts"